<!--
    Korean (ko) — translated from values-de/ (German source of truth).

    Script notes:
    • Hangul (한글) is used throughout. Android renders Hangul via the bundled
      Noto Sans KR font on API 21+; no extra configuration needed.
    • Register: polite formal (합쇼체 / 해요체) as is standard for Korean app UIs.
    • "Binge drinking" → 과음 (gwa-eum) — established Korean public-health term.
    • DHS is kept as "DHS"; WHO as "WHO" (both widely used in Korean).
    • Units: ml, g, % are kept as-is (internationally understood in Korea).
    • day_change_time_value: Korean clock notation uses 시 (si) for hour and
      분 (bun) for minute, but the app displays HH:MM numerically, so the
      German "Uhr" suffix is simply omitted.
    • Counters: Korean uses 개 (gae) for general items; days use 일 (il) or
      the Sino-Korean 일 depending on context. "일" is used for pdf_days_suffix
      and days_count to match the numeric context.
-->
